# Active Directory Basics

**Room:** [TryHackMe – Active Directory Basics](https://tryhackme.com/room/winadbasics)
**Status:** In Completed

## Summary
Introduced core Active Directory concepts: domain objects, security
principals (users, machines), Organizational Units (OUs), and the
Active Directory Users and Computers (ADUC) console.

## Key Concepts
- **Users** — security principals representing people or services;
  authenticated and granted access to network resources
- **Machines** — every domain-joined computer gets an account; acts as
  local admin on its own machine but limited rights domain-wide
- **OUs** — used to organize users/computers by department
  (e.g. IT, Management, Marketing, Sales, R&D) for easier policy management

## Practical Steps
- Navigated `thm.local` domain structure in ADUC
- Created a new Organizational Unit under `thm.local/THM`
- Reviewed existing user accounts (Christine, Robert, Sophie, Thomas)
